<TEXT>
georgio santangelo an avantgarde designer 
known for his elegant clinging fashions has died he was 56 
santangelo died of lung cancer tuesday at st lukesroosevelt 
hospital center 
he was a highly original and imaginative designer said bill 
blass he brought a lot of energy and ability to american 
fashions 
santangelo became famous for his designs that used bodyhugging 
stretch fabrics for comfortable dressy clothing popular with bianca 
jagger faye dunaway and lena horne among others 
many of his ideas have since passed into the mainstream and can 
be seen in the collections of calvin klein jeanpaul gaultier and 
donna karan 
santangelo became a designer by chance in 1967 while working 
as a textile designer the italianborn count took some pieces of 
plastic home one evening and fashioned them into geometric shaped 
jewelry 
the jewelry caught the eye of diana vreeland then editor of 
vogue who published pictures of the work 
santangelo won his first coty award for these designs the 
following year he soon translated his ideas from plastic to 
tiedyed fabrics and entered the fashion business he won his 
second coty in 1970 for his clothes 
santangelo once said i like to do absolutely everything 
because one area always brings ideas for another 
born count giorgio di santangelo in florence he grew up on his 
grandfathers farm in argentina he attended the institute of 
industrial design in barcelona spain and studied art at the 
sorbonne in paris 
he studied with picasso in the south of france before coming to 
the united states in the 1960s to work for the walt disney studies 
in california 
in 1967 he dropped the di and the title from his name to 
make it sound more american 
he is survived by a brother hector imperatrice of rosario 
argentina 
</TEXT>
