home on economic and political freedom have fled to the west through 
hungary since july according to west german estimates 
thousands more in hungary who have outstayed visitors visas 
refuse to go back and are crowding red cross camps in budapest 
where a fifth camp for the refugees is to open friday 
hundreds of likeminded east germans also refuse to leave west 
german diplomatic property in prague and east berlin unless 
guaranteed safe passage to west germany which considers them 
citizens 
most of the east germans managing to flee have done so from 
hungary to austria after hungary in may began removing barbed wire 
and other barriers 
