gov edward d diprete today proposed a 
sweeping plan that would provide academic help to students from the 
third grade through high school and promise graduates money toward 
college costs 
in return parents and children signing up for the rhode island 
childrens crusade would have to obey the law avoid drugs agree 
to work with mentors and tutors have their report cards monitored 
