<TEXT>
morris moe dalitz a gaming pioneer who 
helped develop several major las vegas casinos but was later dogged 
by his early ties to organized crime died early today he was 89 
and had been ill for some time 
dalitz was born near boston and he and his brothers operated a 
chain of cleaners in detroit and cleveland shortly after coming to 
las vegas in 1949 he acquired an ownership interest in the desert 
inn and stardust hotels 
in the early 1950s he joined partners to form paradise 
development co which built the citys convention center a major 
hospital and shopping center and several buildings at the university 
of nevadalas vegas 
