panamanian ambassador juan b sosa a leader of 
forces opposed to gen manuel antonio noriega closed down his 
embassy today and said it would not open until democracy returns to 
panama 
he said he plans to ask the united states for political asylum 
sosa never recognized the february 1988 ouster of president eric 
arturo delvalle and with us government support remained here as 
panamas ambassador 
delvalles term in office under panamas constitution would 
have ended on friday sosa has considered delvalle to be the 
legitimate authority in panama and in view of the deadline 
concluded he could no longer legally stay on as ambassador 
this chapter of the embassy is closed today but you have not 
heard the last sosa said 
he added that noriega will appoint a new president on friday to 
meet constitutional requirements but said that will constitute yet 
another puppet government for panama 
as long as noriega is in power there will be no democracy in 
panama he said 
he said he planned to turn over the embassy keys to the state 
departments office of foreign missions late today 
sosa apparently has been given preliminary assurances his asylum 
request will be granted he said last week he has rented an 
apartment in washington and plans to look for a job 
