<TEXT>
princess anne and mark phillips the royal couple 
rarely seen together on thursday admitted the open secret of their 
life apart with a palace statement that they are separating 
although have no plans to divorce 
the announcement ended rumors of strife that have dogged queen 
elizabeth iis only daughter and her commoner husband for more than 
half their 15year marriage 
it was the second time this century that a marriage in the 
immediate royal family has broken down the queens sister princess 
margaret separated from lord snowdon in 1976 and they divorced two 
years later 
her royal highness the princess royal and capt mark phillips 
have decided to separate on terms agreed between them said the 
short palace statement there are no plans for divorce 
proceedings 
if they want to file for divorce british law requires them to 
live apart for two years 
anne will live at the family estate gatcombe park in western 
england with their two children peter 11 and zara 8 while 
phillips will move to a home nearby the palace said marks father 
maj peter phillips said wednesday night that his son will move to 
aston farm on the estate 
the decision to split up was taken in principle earlier this 
year added a palace spokeswoman the queen who was at her 
balmoral castle in scotland was said by palace sources to be 
saddened but understanding 
anne 39 and phillips 40 have been spending up to half the 
year apart and tabloid newspapers have speculated about 
extramarital attachments for both 
the two avid equestrians met in 1968 at a dinner for the british 
olympic riding team and their glittering 1973 wedding in westminster 
abbey was broadcast to 500 million tv viewers 
anne was attending an international olympic committee meeting in 
puerto rico when the separation was announced and refused to answer 
reporters questions although she appeared unperturbed a source 
close to her said she was upset by the attention 
the princess who is seventh in line to the throne was not due 
back in britain until midseptember she will fly friday to belize 
on a fourday trip on behalf the save the children fund of which 
she is president from there she was scheduled to travel to ecuador 
and bolivia 
phillips who travels widely to teach riding and run various 
equestrian businesses was at gatcombe park 80 miles west of london 
and also was silent 
sharing a passion for horses anne and phillips have competed in 
olympic equestrian events and won riding championships 
but over the years they drifted apart at the 1984 and 1988 
olympics they stayed in different hotels and last year spent their 
15th wedding anniversary thousands of miles apart 
a former captain in the queens dragoon guards phillips 
describes himself as quiet and shy and a farmer at heart 
anne who has a biting wit and downtoearth manner was known as 
her royal haughtiness in the 1970s for her often cold and brisk 
manner 
but that image changed in the early 1980s as newspapers began to 
notice her devoted work for the save the children fund an 
international charity her courage in visiting dangerous corners of 
the globe and her willingness to roll up her sleeves and work for 
the poor and hungry made her one of the most respected members of 
the royal family 
she is a patron of more than 75 charities and 23 military groups 
on april 6 the sun britains biggestcirculation tabloid 
reported it had been handed four stolen letters written to anne by a 
man who turned out to be a palace aide and navy officer tim 
laurence 35 
late in august laurence left the queens service to take command 
of a frigate but was awarded the royal victorian order for 
extraordinary important or personal services to the sovereign or 
the royal family 
phillips said at that time that his marriage was fine and 
happy 
barbara cartland romantic novelist and a stepgrandmother of 
annes sisterinlaw princess diana said changing times and public 
morals played a part in the breakup 
up to now royalty was on a pedestal they werent treated as 
ordinary human beings she said now youve treated them like 
human beings im not surprised they behave like human beings 
