<TEXT>
drivers of cars equipped with antilock brakes 
could soon be getting a break on their auto insurance rates 
in a move that could set a precedent for other major insurance 
companies allstate insurance co announced wednesday it is offering 
a 10 percent discount on three major autopolicy coverages for cars 
with antilock brakes 
this discount in effect is the first of its kind for a major 
carrier said greg rossiter a spokesman for the company based in 
the chicago suburb of northbrook 
the only other us insurance company currently offering an 
antilock brake system discount is usaa of san antonio texas a 
firm which provides insurance to military personnel and their 
dependents rossiter said 
antilock brakes use an onboard computer to control wheel speed 
during braking allowing faster and safer stops without skidding or 
loss of steering control 
theres no question that the antilock brake system provides a 
remarkable amount of braking protection that is not available in 
regular brake systems rossiter said 
william geen senior vicepresident of ccc information services 
inc a chicagobased firm that evaluates car losses for the 
insurance industry said he also has found that antilock brakes are 
effective 
its certainly been proven that the antilock brake system 
works very well and more manufacturers are offering it 
geen said he expected other insurance companies to follow 
allstates example in offering the antilock brake discount 
geen said there are few cars on the road with antilock brakes 
but they should be available as an optional or standard feature on 
more 1990 model cars 
the antilock system was introduced about six years ago and 
until recently has only been available on luxury cars it is now 
being offered as an option on more moderately priced autos but no 
statistics are available as to how many cars now on the road in the 
united states have antilock brakes rossiter said 
the new discount offered by allstate a subsidiary of sears 
roebuck amp co covers cars equipped with fourwheel antilock brake 
systems it provides for 10 percent off three coverages that are 
part of an auto policy bodily injury property damage liability 
and collision 
